Biker reacts in a flash and prevents worse
On Friday evening, a traffic accident occurred on the country road between Machtolsheim and Merklingen, in which a motorcyclist was only slightly injured thanks to his quick reaction.
Car driver overlooks biker
At around 9:30 p.m., a 44-year-old driver of a VW coming from Merklingen wanted to turn left onto the state road 1230 in the direction of Machtolsheim.
In doing so, she overlooked the 24-year-old motorcyclist coming from Nellingen, who had the right of way.
